{{Accessory
| Name=Atari Keypad
| Guid=3000-91
| Deck=Keypad controller for the Atari 2600
| Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/18/185326/2781549-4316659349-con_A.jpg}}

<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"2781549-4316659349-con_A.jpg","path":"18\/185326\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"scale_small,scale_super,square_mini,square_small,square_tiny,square_medium,scale_tiny,square_avatar,scale_medium,scale_large,scale_avatar,screen_medium,screen_kubrick","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
A limited number of Atari 2600 games (and [[Games/Basic_Programming|Basic Programming]]) use these keypads for input. They were sold separately in pairs, with an overlay for Basic Programming. The standard version features a slide-lock mechanism to connect two controllers together, for a single, extra wide keypad. Several functionally identical controllers were produced. Star Raiders was packed with the Video Touch Pad, and a game-specific overlay. The Kid's Controller was a larger, blue-colored version.
Compatible titles include:
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;Basic Programming&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Brain_Games|Brain Games]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Codebreaker|Codebreaker]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/A_Game_of_Concentration|Game of Concentration]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Hunt_And_Score|Hunt andamp;amp;amp; Score]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Videocart_15_Memory_Match|Memory Match]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;Testcart&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Alpha_Beam_with_Ernie|Alpha Beam with Ernie]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Big_Birds_Egg_Catch|Big Bird's Egg Catch]]&lt;/p&gt;
* &lt;p style="" data-right-indent="0" data-left-indent="0"&gt;[[Games/Cookie_Monster_Munch|Cookie Monster Munch]]&lt;/p&gt;
