{{Accessory | Name=DualSense Edge | Guid=3000-190 | Deck=A high-performance, customizable controller developed by Sony for the PlayStation 5. | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/3401943-3469008311-6d2cc.jpg}}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3401943-3469008311-6d2cc.jpg","path":"0\/1992\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"square_small,scale_super,square_tiny,square_medium,scale_medium,scale_small,square_mini,screen_medium,scale_large,scale_avatar,screen_kubrick,square_avatar","caption":null},"background":{"file":"3401747-screenshot2022-08-23at2.33.55pm.png","path":"0\/1992\/","mime":"image\/png","sizes":"square_medium,square_tiny,square_small,scale_super,scale_medium,screen_kubrick_wide,square_mini","caption":""}}' />
==Overview== This [[Platforms/PlayStation_5|PlayStation 5]] controller was first unveiled during Gamescom 2022's Opening Night Live.

{{Accessory | Name=DualShock 2 | Guid=3000-30 | Deck=The DualShock 2 is Sony's standard controller for the PlayStation 2. | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/0/2164/1270989-a_dual_shock_2.jpg}}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"1270989-a_dual_shock_2.jpg","path":"0\/2164\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"square_avatar,square_small,scale_medium,screen_medium,scale_small,scale_large,scale_avatar,square_mini,square_tiny,square_medium,scale_tiny,scale_super,screen_kubrick","caption":""},"background":[]}' /> The DualShock 2 was announced and released alongside the [[Platforms/PlayStation_2|PlayStation 2]]. Apart from color, logo, and number of screws, it is visually identical to the original [[Accessories/DualShock_Analog_Controller|DualShock controller.]]
Improvements over its predecessor include lighter weight, pressure sensitivity on the action buttons, and enhanced analog stick mobility.

{{Accessory | Name=DualShock Analog Controller | Guid=3000-1 | Deck=The DualShock controller designed by Sony Computer Entertainment was the third controller released for the original PlayStation. Its design continued through the next several generations of Sony's consoles. | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/3395552-5828035553-duals.jpg}}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3395552-5828035553-duals.jpg","path":"0\/1992\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"square_medium,scale_super,square_small,scale_large,square_mini,scale_small,square_avatar,screen_medium,screen_kubrick,square_tiny,scale_avatar,scale_medium","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
==Overview== The DualShock is the iconic and critically acclaimed [[Platforms/PlayStation|PlayStation]] controller on which [[Companies/Sony_Corporation|Sony]] has based all of its subsequent controller designs. The DualShock was developed by Sony for use with the original PlayStation and released in [[Locations/Japan|Japan]] in 1997. The PlayStation's original controller lacked analog control and force feedback. The 1999 game [[Games/Ape_Escape|Ape Escape]] was the first to require a DualShock for play, and Sony quickly adopted the controller as the PlayStation standard, packing it in with subsequent versions of the console.

{{Accessory | Name=GameCube Game Boy Advance Cable | Guid=3000-149 | Deck=This official link cable released by Nintendo in December 2001 allows for various connectivity features between the console and handheld versions of games. | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/3396053-5543323328-2560p.jpg}}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"3396053-5543323328-2560p.jpg","path":"0\/1992\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"scale_medium,square_medium,scale_small,square_tiny,square_small,scale_super,square_mini,scale_avatar,scale_large,screen_kubrick,square_avatar,screen_medium","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
